Package enums

package enums
The enums package contains Java enumerations that represent a set of named constants.

Enums in this package are used to define fixed sets of values that represent different states, types, or options within the application. They enhance code readability and maintainability by providing a clear and self-documenting way to represent specific, predefined values.

Enums are often used in switch statements, configuration settings, and situations where a finite set of options is expected.
